---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Hayaan Dangra"
  description="High school senior at Alliance Academy exploring cyber security, healthcare tech, and math visualizations."
>
  <section class="hero section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Me</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bio section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content">
        <p>
          I'm Hayaan Dangra, a high school senior at Alliance Academy in Georgia. Born to immigrant parents and growing up in a rural community, I was very lonely. I spent lots of time with a pencil and a notebook. I found that the structured nature of math quantified the uncertainty of life into an objective truth that could be deduced through logic.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's still how I work. I've been on math teams since elementary school — Mathletes, UGA Math Competition, KSU, MathLeague. I placed 2nd at State in FBLA Data Analysis (NYC air quality proposal). I compete in cybersecurity (Cyberavengers, NCL, CyberPatriot) because math is the underlying mechanism that allows the Internet to function.
        </p>
        <p>
          For the past 3 years, I've been CFO of Elote King, my family's food business. I use regression and prediction algorithms based on market data to make financial decisions. I also work as an AI Automation Developer at Pure Tech Innovation, where I build workflows that have increased productivity by 100%. Everything I do — business, code, security, teaching — is math applied to real problems.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="current-work section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What I'm Into Right Now</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Math Explorations</h3>
          <p>County-level GHP nominee, building interactive visualizations to explore chaos theory, prime patterns, and wave mathematics. Game theory is where I connect math to interests I haven't discovered yet.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Cyber Security</h3>
          <p>Cyberavengers, NCL, CyberPatriot. Network security isn't just protocols — it's number theory, cryptography, and probability. CompTIA Network+ certified.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>AI & Automation</h3>
          <p>Building workflows at Pure Tech Innovation with Claude, N8N, and Cursor. Automation is applied logic — turning repetitive tasks into functions that can be optimized.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Teaching</h3>
          <p>At Creative Labs Learning Center — teaching forces you to break math down. If you can't explain why a loop starts at zero, you don't actually understand iteration.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Education & Achievements</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <ul class="stack-list">
          <li>Alliance Academy for Innovation, Class of 2027</li>
          <li>GPA 4.3, SAT 1540 (790 Math)</li>
          <li>AP Calc AB/BC, AP CS A, AP CS Principles, AP Precalculus, AP Bio</li>
          <li>CompTIA Network+ Certified</li>
          <li>FBLA Data Analysis — 2nd at State</li>
          <li>Math competitions: UGA, KSU, MathLeague, Mathletes</li>
          <li>County-level GHP Nominee</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tech-stack section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>My Stack</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <ul class="stack-list">
          <li>HTML, CSS, JavaScript</li>
          <li>Astro (static sites)</li>
          <li>AI automation (Claude, N8N, Cursor, Perplexity)</li>
          <li>SEO & analytics</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="next section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What's Next</h2>
      <div class="content">
        <p>
          I'm looking for the kind of challenge where I can go deeper — whether that's GHP this summer, a cyber security project, or the next business problem that needs a website.
        </p>
        <p>
          <!-- TODO: Replace # with Hayaan's actual profile URLs when created -->
          If you want to follow what I'm building, find me on <a href="#">X</a> or <a href="#">LinkedIn</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .bio,
  .tech-stack,
  .next {
    background-color: var(--white);
  }

  .stack {
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
  }

  .current-work {
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .content p {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
  }

  h2 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .card {
    background-color: var(--white);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--blue);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }

  .card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  }

  .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--blue);
  }

  .card p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .stack-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .stack-list li {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    position: relative;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  .stack-list li::before {
    content: "→";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--blue);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .next .content {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .next a {
    font-weight: 700;
  }
</style>
